AGI - A plane of the Air Force, with Palestinian children on board > needy care, landed in the evening in Milan and will continue its journey to Pisa and Rome. The small patients, accompanied by their families and a medical team, will be immediately transferred to the Italian hospitals to receive the necessary care.
"Behind every mission like this there are stories of suffering, but also of hope - said the Minister of Defense, Guido Crosetto >- these children, forced to leave their land to be healed, represent the most fragile face of a conflict that saves no one. Italy is not indifferent: We will continue to work to ensure assistance and protection to those who need it. A special thanks goes to all those who made this operation possible: the staff of the Armed Forces, Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation, and Civil Protection."
<div </div
This mission, we read in a note, is part of a broader humanitarian commitment that sees Italy at the forefront of assisting the civilian population of Gaza. In addition to the health evacuation of vulnerable patients, our country actively participates in the international EUBAM-RAFAH mission, facilitating the transit of wounded and sick to the Rafah Pass, guarantees the transport of humanitarian aid by air and sea and provided health support with the Navy Volcano Ship. > Italy thus confirms its role as Nation committed to international solidarity, with the aim of offering concrete help to those who are more affected by the dramatic consequences of the conflict, concludes the note.&nbsp;<br> &nbsp;
